snippet.title: Top 10 Best Catherine O’Hara Quotes on Schitt’s Creek
snippet.description:
"Fold in the cheese!" Join us as we celebrate the linguistic masterpiece that is Moira Rose! Her vocabulary is as extravagant as her wig collection, and we're counting down the most hilarious, bewildering, and utterly preposterous utterances from Schitt's Creek's beloved matriarch. Which Moira-ism left you absolutely befuddled? Our countdown includes gems like "What you did was impulsive, capricious, and melodramatic... but it was also wrong," "I have asked you thrice now for a towel," "Stop acting like a disgruntled pelican," and more! Tell us your favorite Moira Rose quote in the comments below!
